<title>USA: USLIFE extends stock repurchase program.</title>
<headline>USLIFE extends stock repurchase program.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1996-10-22</dateline>
<text>
<p>USLIFE Corp said Tuesday it had extended its stock repurchase program through November 1997, authorizing the purchase of up to 1.5 million common shares or convertible preferred equivalents.</p>
<p>Excluding treasury stock, USLIFE Corp had 34,361,790 common shares issued and outstanding as of September 30.</p>
<p>Since the stock repurchase program began in 1981, USLIFE has bought back 26 million shares of its common stock at a cost of about $382 million.</p>
